def: Following by consequence; consequent; deducible. [R.]"Consectary impieties." Sir T. Browne.
Commensality. [Obs.]Daniel . . . declined pagan commensation. Sir T. Browne.
Indented with small concave curves, as the edge of a bordure,bend, or the like.
Not using prayer; habitually neglecting prayer to God; withoutprayer. "The next time you go prayerless to bed." Baxter.-- Prayer"less*ly, adv.-- Prayer"less*ness, n.
A dark-colored, basic, igneous rock, composed essentially ofpyroxene and a triclinic feldspar with magnetic iron. By many authorsit is considered equivalent to a coarse-grained basalt.
The public officer who has charge of a subtreasury. [U. S.]
A very small coin; a doit.
A morbid induration, as of a gland; stste of being scirrhous.
